{{see|Scot}}
==English==
===Etymology===
From Old Norse [[skot]], later influenced by Old French ''[[escot]]'' (modern [[écot]]), itself of Germanic origin.  Compare [[shot]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/skɒt/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# (''UK Historical'') A local [[tax]], paid originally to the lord or ruler and later to a sheriff.

